{
  "texts": [
    "Finally, we analyze potential differences in those RU users that perform a hard-switch to UA from those that do not (see Table 3).",
    "We find that there are significant differences (p < 0.05) in the median in various user characteristics between the two groups using a two-sided chi-squared test (no distributional assumptions required).",
    "Users switching have more followers (+54.5%, χ 2 (1) = 8.223, p = 0.004), a higher tweet frequency (+47.7%, χ 2 (1) = 5.352, p = 0.021) as well as a higher like frequency (+48.9%, χ 2 (1) = 5.352, p = 0.021) and published more Ukraine geo-tagged tweets during the study period (+49.1%, χ 2 (1) = 10.639, p = 0.001), whereas there are only small nonsignificant differences in account age (+12.2%, χ 2 (1) = 3.196, p = 0.07) and followings (+13.8%, χ 2 (1) = 2.023, p = 0.16).",
    "n = 1067 users in the no switch group, n = 296 users in the switch group.",
    "Column 2 reports the median of the respective user characteristic for those Russian users that do not perform a statistically significant hard-switch to Ukrainian with the outbreak of the war, column 3 for the users that do."
  ]
}